<item>
            <title>[LU-19314] IPv6 sanity-lnet test_228: Can&apos;t find test in current session</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19314</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/00485604-27eb-480a-8b2a-02ca808d6094&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/00485604-27eb-480a-8b2a-02ca808d6094&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_228 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;No nodes added successfully, deleting group servers
Group is deleted
Test: --batch brw_rw --concurrency 16 --from clients --to servers --distribute 1:1 brw read size=1m
Test: --batch brw_rw --concurrency 16 --from clients --to servers --distribute 1:1 brw write size=1m
Stat: --count 1 --delay 15 --bw --mbs clients servers
Reader error: &apos;Object not found&apos; at 0
Reader error: &apos;Object not found&apos; at 0
Can&apos;t find test in current session
Stop LST rw - Sun Aug 31 15:03:33 UTC 2025
 sanity-lnet test_228: @@@@@@ FAIL: LST returned non-zero rc = 255 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/116149&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/116149&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.58.1.el8_10.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/116149&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/116149&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.58.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fails repeatedly during review-dne-ipv6 test session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be useful if sanity-lnet returned a proper error string instead of failing with a numeric code. &lt;/p&gt;







&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-lnet test_228 - LST returned non-zero rc = 255&lt;/p&gt;</description>
