                            <comment id="474495" author="yujian" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2025 23:49:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19323&quot; title=&quot;lnet_selftest.sh support for ipv6 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19323&quot;&gt;LU-19323&lt;/a&gt; is resolved, the subtest can be removed from the always except list.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="472710" author="adilger" created="Wed, 24 Sep 2025 04:22:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, test will be skipped by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/61337&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/61337&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19323&quot; title=&quot;lnet_selftest.sh support for ipv6 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19323&quot;&gt;LU-19323&lt;/a&gt; tests: add more sanity-lnet subtests into IPv6 except list&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471682" author="pjones" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 19:02:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should we just be skipping the test for now then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="471671" author="adilger" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2025 18:03:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19323&quot; title=&quot;lnet_selftest.sh support for ipv6 &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19323&quot;&gt;LU-19323&lt;/a&gt; because lnet-selftest does not support IPv6 yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
